(1361, 429, '_field_81', 'During this week, client was happy, receptive, playful, and calm. Client was easily engaged with technician. Client was pleasant, friendly, and would actively listen to technician. Parent, Technician and client worked on bathroom obligations this week. When client felt the need to move his bowels he would call parent or technician use the bathroom without going on himself. Client and technician also worked on homework. This week’s homework consisted of working with the letter H using penmanship. Client was to trace the letter H on homework sheet. Technician and client also worked on coloring each object to its nature of origin. All objects started with the letter H, like hat, heart, hand, and house. Teacher even informed parent that client was asked to use a word that begins with the letter H, and client said hug without any assistance from teacher. Technician and client worked on calendar days of the week, money concept, and motor skills. By using the WII, playing boxing and bowling. '),
(1362, 429, '_field_82', 'N/A'),
(1363, 429, '_field_83', '1. The first goal for the week’s session is to get client to actively listen, in addition to follow Technician direction, and learn how to implement behavioral modification techniques.\n2. The second goal for the week’s session is to practice modeling, operant conditioning, and calming techniques with client.  \n3. The last goal for the week’s session was to implement usage of motor skills.  \nPlan:  Technician plan is to gradually help client use modification techniques, work on motor skills, toilet training, and perhaps use positive reinforcement. Last, work on implementing behavioral modification techniques, so client doesn’t easily get bored, or agitated when things doesn’t go his way.\n'),
(1364, 429, '_field_84', 'When observing and gathering information on client. Technician noticed client was very attentive this week. Whenever, technician and parent would come up with different ways to approach the bathroom obligations. Client would listen and follow directions as instructed in order to receive a reward. Supervisor came by this week to see how client is doing. We discussed some things he needs to improve with such as brushing the teeth, putting on clothes, telling time, and bathing self. We also mentioned what has improved such as washing hands, removing clothes, disposing of trash, and helping with washing clothes. Supervisor was advised that client is attempting to remove bowels without messing on himself. Supervisor was also notified that client has been cooperating when working on homework tasks with technician. Client’s brother birthday was this week. Therefore, parents, brother, technician, and client went bowling. '),
(1365, 429, '_field_85', 'Client refused to bowl, due to the large crowd that surrounded him. So technician and client walked around and went outside in order to avoid any confrontation. '),
