(1819, 461, '_field_90', 'This session, ISS assisted youth with his meal. ISS worked with him on homework and activities to promote listening and self-regulation. Youth worked with on positive social skills by targeting specific behaviors such as his anger when he doesn’t get his phone when he wants. ISS played Simon Says with youth to help encourage self-regulation/impulses. Youth was able to utilize the playground which allowed him to climb, swing, run and jump. These activities help strengthening gross motor development. ISS continued to promote his ability to stay on task and organization skills (putting completed homework in his folder) which help promote academic development. Youth worked on a puzzle that maps out a community market and fine motor development worksheets (mazes, same &amp; different, cut and paste).'),
(1820, 461, '_field_58', 'Next session youth will continue working on homework and activities to promote listening and self-regulation. Continue working with youth on positive social skills by targeting specific behaviors. ISS will continue using games in the activity that have directives to strengthening self-regulation. Continue work with activities which strengthening fine/gross motor development. ISS will continue to encourage staying on task and organization skills which help promote academic development. '),
