(1913, 465, '_field_90', 'Clinician met with family on 10/16/17 from 6PM to 8PM. Present in the home was mom, dad, KH, and  NH. The purpose of the session was to transition family to the end of services. The family completed a mindfulness game in which each member discussed things that upset them, things that family members do that upset them, things themselves do that upset them and then concluded with what they are grateful for that other members do in their family. The game was to practice using kind words, being mindful, listen and discuss feeling without going into an aggress conversation. All members were able to complete the task and enjoyed it even if it was still difficult to discuss some topics. The family has progress a lot during the clinician’s time there. No further sessions were scheduled at this time.  \n\n\nName: Diana Dominguez\n'),
