(31, 1, '2017-07-28 23:49:26', '2017-07-28 23:49:26', 'New Care associates count with professional providers who teach children with any developmental disability to be more self-sufficient and productive, Using strategies such as role play, Active listening, modeling and other strategies to motivate individuals with incapacity to self-care, follow instructions, learning instrumental ADL’s, using a telephone, washing dishes, preparing a simple meal, changing bed linens, the ability to manage money, dress themselves, be aware of danger in home and in the community, which is going to enable the individual to live independently in the community.\r\n\r\n<strong>How can parents benefit from using your services? </strong>\r\n\r\nAs ISS provider we also support the parents, listening their concerns, educating them about their child/youth condition and addressing the needs of each of them. Working as a team new care offer the family a source of tranquility knowing that our agency will work with them until the goals has been met with the youth.\r\n\r\n<strong>Do you have any testimonials?</strong>\r\n\r\nOur current clients are very pleased with the services. They have seen improvement in different areas such as tying their shoes independently, being toilet trained and improving in personal hygiene skills. And they feel a relief knowing that they have the support and guidance that they needed it.\r\n\r\n<strong>Updated mission statement (if that has changed)</strong>\r\n\r\nNew care associates mission is to serve the family in the community to bring them together from the child’s family and others facilitators to create a model to support the family situation. Using the Wraparound system which is focus on individualized care management process for youths with serious or complex needs, as our main Pilate to serve with excellence.', 'About Us', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '8-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-07-28 23:49:26', '2017-07-28 23:49:26', '', 8, 'http://localhost/newcare-full/8-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(32, 1, '2017-07-28 23:50:19', '2017-07-28 23:50:19', '<div class=\"nc-content-wrapper\">\r\n<h2>FAQs (Frequently Asked Questions)</h2>\r\n<b>Who We Are </b>\r\nWe are provider of mental health services to children ages 4-21 and families with mental health issues. By mental health, we are referring to behavioral,  Attention Deficit Disorder (ADD), Attention-Deficit/Hyperactivity Disorder (ADHD), Autism, Obsessive Compulsive Disorder (OCD), Obsessive–Compulsive Personality Disorder (OCDD), and  Pervasive Developmental Disorders (PDD) to name a few.\r\n<h3>PARENTS / GUARDIANS</h3>\r\n<strong>What insurance do I need to have?</strong>\r\nWe only accept clients with Medicaid at this time.\r\n\r\n<strong>What is the process of getting you to work with my child?</strong>\r\n\r\nIf you, as the parent or guardian, notice any behavioral changes in your child that causes concern, contact Perform Care (1-877-652-7624). They will perform a triage, which is a thorough clinical assessment of your child. Then upon approval, they will contact the local referring agencies for professional assistance. The local agencies will then refer your child to our program if you reside within the counties we serve.\r\n\r\n<strong>What generally takes place at the first appointment?</strong>\r\n\r\nThe Clinician or Behavioral Assistant will perform an assessment, engage both the parent and child, and disburse pertinent information such as what to expect along with the frequency of visits.  The Clinician will also present forms and agreements for parent signatures.\r\n\r\n<strong>Do your Clinicians / Behavioral Assistants have any certifications? How can I trust them?</strong>\r\n\r\nClinicians have Sociology degrees with an LSW (License in Social Work). Both Clinicians /Behavioral Assistants have extensive training in Behavioral Counseling to ensure that the interaction with your child is effective and professional.\r\n\r\n<strong>Are there any expenses the parent needs to cover?</strong>\r\n\r\nAll expenses are covered by Medicaid.\r\n\r\n<strong>How will my child benefit from your services?</strong>\r\n\r\nOur Clinicians / Behavioral Assistants will teach your child to be more self-sufficient and productive by utilizing strategies such as role play, active listening, modeling and other distinctive methods.  One of our main goals is to educate our clients to follow proper instructions that will result in self-care by employing instrumental ADL (Active Daily Living) techniques.  In our program, your child will learn the following skills to enable them to live independently within the community:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Using a telephone</li>\r\n 	<li>Washing dishes</li>\r\n 	<li>Preparing a simple meal</li>\r\n 	<li>Changing bed linens</li>\r\n 	<li>Managing money</li>\r\n 	<li>Dressing themselves</li>\r\n 	<li>Being aware of danger</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Does the parent benefit from the program as well as the child? </strong>\r\n\r\nAs an ISS provider we also support the parents, listening their concerns, educating them about their child\'s condition and addressing the needs of each of them. Working as a team new care offer the family a source of tranquility knowing that our agency will work with them until the goals has been met with the youth.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>(from other Agencies – referrals)</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>What is the process of getting you to work with a particular child?  (Their contact form will be different from the parents’.)</li>\r\n 	<li>What else will you need from us in addition to filling out the referral form?</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>General Questions</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>I’m interested in working for your company. What’s the process to find out if there are any openings?</li>\r\n 	<li>How can I apply?</li>\r\n 	<li>After I apply, how long is the hiring process?</li>\r\n 	<li>What are they compensation types? (Health insurance or not, bi-weekly or weekly pay, based on what)</li>\r\n 	<li>What’s the onboarding process?</li>\r\n 	<li>Where are you located?</li>\r\n 	<li>What is the best way to contact your company and how soon will I receive a response?</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Any other frequently asked questions and answers would be super helpful. </strong>\r\n\r\n&lt;/div\r\n\r\n</div>', 'FAQ', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '10-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-07-28 23:50:19', '2017-07-28 23:50:19', '', 10, 'http://localhost/newcare-full/10-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
